Love this question 👌 — this is exactly how you move from “working prototype” to “proper product plan”.

Below are **many short, atomic Trello-ready subtasks** grouped by theme. Each one is small, actionable, and clear.

You can literally copy-paste these as Trello cards.

---

# 🟢 EPIC 1: Code Matching & Snyk Integration

### 🔹 Subtasks

1. Refactor Snyk SARIF parsing into separate module (`snyk_loader.py`)
2. Add validation if `snyk-code-output.json` is missing
3. Add error handling for malformed SARIF
4. Improve fuzzy match threshold logic
5. Replace fuzzy matching with top-3 match selection
6. Add similarity threshold slider in UI
7. Add match confidence badge (color-coded)
8. Add fallback when no snippet found in repo
9. Add support for multi-line snippet matching
10. Log matching score for debugging
11. Add option to toggle “strict match mode”
12. Add test case for incorrect snippet matching
13. Optimize matching performance for large Snyk files
14. Add embedding-based semantic matching (future upgrade)
15. Cache parsed Snyk results using `st.cache_data`

